Commentary Text: Boult to A Russell, out Bowled!! Gone now. If anyone needed a sample of how to get Russell out, just watch this from Boult. No fuss or drama. The old-fashioned yorker - still gets you wickets even today. Will do so after 100 years as well. Just that you have to get it right. Boult did, slipped it under A Russell's swinging bat and it clipped middle and leg. Superb bowling and that wicket could mean a difference of 20 at least to the eventual score. No big celebrations from Boult, just a fist pump. Replays show that it was delivered cross-seam as well. A Russell b Boult 41(12) [6s-6]

Commentary Text: Chawla to Roy, wide, out Stumped!! Smart stumping from Karthik and the last match hero falls cheaply. Nicely bowled by Chawla as well, he pre-empted that Roy was coming down the track and slid this one down the leg-side, Roy stepped forward, the momentum took him further ahead, he turned around in panic, but Karthik had by then removed one of the stumps.
